# Converting Markdown to PowerPoint - Instructions

Since I cannot create a binary PowerPoint file directly, here are several options to convert the markdown presentation to PowerPoint:

## Option 1: Use Pandoc (Recommended)
1. Install Pandoc: https://pandoc.org/installing.html
2. Run this command in PowerShell:
   ```
   pandoc CAST_Imaging_MCP_Server_Presentation.md -o CAST_Imaging_MCP_Server_Presentation.pptx
   ```

## Option 2: Manual Copy-Paste
1. Open the markdown file: CAST_Imaging_MCP_Server_Presentation.md
2. Create a new PowerPoint presentation
3. Copy each slide section and paste into PowerPoint slides
4. Format as needed

## Option 3: Online Converters
- Use online tools like:
  - Slides.com
  - Beautiful.ai
  - Canva (supports markdown import)

## Option 4: Use Marp (Markdown Presentation Ecosystem)
1. Install Marp: https://marp.app/
2. Open the markdown file in Marp
3. Export as PowerPoint

The markdown file contains all the content structured for easy conversion to slides.